# ==========================================
# VALIDATION TESTS - 400 Bad Request
# ==========================================
# Test validation với các request không hợp lệ
# ==========================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### Test 1: Missing Email - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "No Email User",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# {
#   "status": 400,
#   "error": "Bad Request",
#   "message": "Validation failed: {email=Email is required}",
#   "timestamp": "..."
# }

###

### Test 2: Missing Name - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# {
#   "status": 400,
#   "error": "Bad Request",
#   "message": "Validation failed: {name=Name is required}",
#   "timestamp": "..."
# }

###

### Test 3: Missing Both Name and Email - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# Multiple validation errors

###

### Test 4: Empty Name - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# @NotBlank catches empty string

###

### Test 5: Whitespace-Only Name - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "   ",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# @NotBlank catches whitespace

###

### Test 6: Name Too Long (> 100 chars) - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "12345678901234567890123456789012345678901234567890123456789012345678901234567890123456789012345678901",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# {
#   "status": 400,
#   "error": "Bad Request",
#   "message": "Validation failed: {name=Name must be between 1 and 100 characters}",
#   "timestamp": "..."
# }

###

### Test 7: Phone Too Long (> 20 chars) - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "012345678901234567890"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# {
#   "status": 400,
#   "error": "Bad Request",
#   "message": "Validation failed: {phone=Phone must not exceed 20 characters}",
#   "timestamp": "..."
# }

###

### Test 8: Invalid Email Format - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# {
#   "status": 400,
#   "error": "Bad Request",
#   "message": "Validation failed: {email=Email must be a valid email address}",
#   "timestamp": "..."
# }

###

### Test 9: Email Without @ - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "emailexample.com",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request

###

### Test 10: Email Without Domain - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request

###

### Test 11: Multiple Validation Errors - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "phone": "012345678901234567890123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# {
#   "status": 400,
#   "error": "Bad Request",
#   "message": "Validation failed: {name=Name is required, email=Email must be a valid email address, phone=Phone must not exceed 20 characters}",
#   "timestamp": "..."
# }

###

### Test 12: All Fields Invalid - 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": null,
  "email": null,
  "phone": "012345678901234567890123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request
# Multiple validation errors for all fields

###

### Test 13: PUT with Missing Name - 400 Bad Request
# Validation cũng áp dụng cho PUT
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "updated@example.com",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request

###

### Test 14: PUT with Invalid Email - 400 Bad Request
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "not-valid",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### Expected Response:
# HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request

###

### Giải thích Validation Flow:

# 1. Request gửi đến Controller
# 2. @Valid annotation trigger validation
# 3. Spring validate theo annotations trong UserRequest:
#    - @NotBlank: Check not null, not empty, not whitespace
#    - @Size: Check length
#    - @Email: Check email format
# 4. Nếu validation FAIL:
#    → Throw MethodArgumentNotValidException
#    → GlobalExceptionHandler catch
#    → Trả về HTTP 400 Bad Request
# 5. Nếu validation PASS:
#    → Tiếp tục vào Service layer
#    → Business logic validation (email duplicate → 409)
#    → Save vào database
